  <section class="lp-section" id="changes">
    <h2><span class="lp-num">09</span><a href="#changes">Changes</a></h2>
    <p>
      We may revise these Terms as the project evolves. Material changes are reflected by the
      &ldquo;Last updated&rdquo; date above. Continued use of the Site or Software after a change
      constitutes acceptance of the revised Terms.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="lp-section" id="law">
    <h2><span class="lp-num">10</span><a href="#law">Governing law</a></h2>
    <p>
      These Terms are governed by the laws of the jurisdiction in which the Charter project
      maintainers are established, without regard to conflict-of-law principles. Nothing here limits
      any non-waivable statutory rights you may have as a consumer.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="lp-section" id="contact">
    <h2><span class="lp-num">11</span><a href="#contact">Contact</a></h2>
    <p>
      Questions about these Terms? Reach us at
      <a href="mailto:legal@use-charter.dev">legal@use-charter.dev</a> or open an issue on our
      <a href="https://github.com/use-charter/charter" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub repository</a>.
    </p>
  </section>
</Legal>
